I've been running a random seeded weekly double elimination league over the course of 2-3 hours. At least 3 times I have had all the matches played wiped out and the players reseeded. Luckily we could figure out who was going to play who but I've since been having to take screen captures to make sure we know where we are in the tourney.    It would be great to have the app save the progress on a device/cloud and update after every change to prevent this.  If it were not for this issue it would be 5 star.
replyContent: Hi Rob, that's odd. By default the app stores the tournament after every action (match decision, score input, etc.). Every tournament that has been started can be continued via the tournament archive (in case you close the app, etc.). Can you tell me what device and Android version you are using - please let me know (feedback.versus@gmail.com).

replyContent: Hi Inita, I'm that sorry the seeding isn't working for you. It should work like this: create 2 round robin tournaments with 4 players each - no need for teams. After the two RR-tournaments - create the bracket (there is no feature to transition from multiple RRs to a bracket yet). Pls write me at feedback.versus@gmail.com if you have any questions.
